From 8e0866fa45bb457169afc4d83e35c62e1cb63f0c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Abhinav Ayyapasetti <aabhinav@windriver.com>
Date: Wed, 25 Feb 2026 12:30:39 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] Remove auto-include of keystone::policy class

Rebased to puppet-module-keystone 25.0.0-4

The puppet-keystone module auto-includes keystone::policy class
without allowing custom policies to be passed. This prevents
StarlingX from injecting custom policy rules.

Remove the auto-include so StarlingX can declare the class
explicitly with custom policies parameter.

Signed-off-by: Abhinav Ayyapasetti <aabhinav@windriver.com>
---
 manifests/init.pp | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/manifests/init.pp b/manifests/init.pp
index 30fcaaf..febdefc 100644
--- a/manifests/init.pp
+++ b/manifests/init.pp
@@ -463,7 +463,6 @@ class keystone(
 
   include keystone::deps
   include keystone::logging
-  include keystone::policy
 
   if $client_package_ensure != undef {
     warning('The client_package_ensure parameter is deprecated and has no effect.')
-- 
